research_insight_text_link.research_insight_description: Mocean Energy focuses on advancing wave energy conversion technology. Their research includes a hinged raft for a wave energy conversion device (WEC), featuring two buoyant bodies connected in a way that allows them to come into contact, optimizing storage and functionality. This innovation reflects their commitment to enhancing the efficiency and practicality of harnessing wave power, contributing to the zero-carbon transition.

overview_description.description:
Mocean Energy develops new technologies that can harness the power of waves and accelerate the transition to a zero-carbon world.

The company was founded in 2015 and is headquartered in Edinburgh, United Kingdom.

identifier.value: Cameron McNatt Managing Director @ Mocean Energy

properties.growth_insight_description: Mocean Energy may be growing as it has recently received significant funding for its wave energy device, with a reported $3.7 million secured for further development. The company is also advancing its commercialization plans, attracting new investors to support its initiatives. Additionally, Mocean Energy is working on developing a 250Kw wave machine in Orkney, which indicates an expansion of its operations and technological advancements in the renewable energy sector.

about_short_description.short_description: Mocean Energy develops new technologies that can harness the power of waves and accelerate the transition to a zero-carbon world.

product.name: Blue Horizon
product.description: A large wave energy converter designed for deployment in wave farms to deliver grid-scale electricity.

product.name: Blue Star
product.description: A compact wave energy converter intended to power a variety of subsea applications such as control systems and autonomous underwater vehicles.

product.name: Blue X
product.description: A prototype model for testing Mocean Energy's hinged-raft design in real sea conditions, providing data for the development of Blue Star and Blue Horizon.
